    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nExecuting `nvim_set_hl()` with boolean fields set to `false` can give incorrect results.\n\nBisected to 4d04d0123d25 from #37546 (@glepnir).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. `:lua vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'AAA', { underdouble = true, underdashed = false })`\n3. `:hi AAA` - shows that it is undercurl instead of underdouble.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSetting boolean highlight attributes to `false` is possible and has no side effects.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2707+gc9e961994b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, \n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n6.19.9-arch1-1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
